{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there were some who apparently were hidden and then-- but they seeked out even the most assimilated Jews who became converted, and so on, because Hitler did not consider anybody-- he considered everybody Jewish who had even a single grandparent as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mean, this is a historical fact.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Anyway, so these people in Vienna, who-- diminished by the fact that a lot of them still had the opportunity to run away.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I must say that the Austrian and German Jews were the only two nations' Jews who had still the opportunity to go.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because it was before the Second World War broke out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And at that time, the Germans were interested just to get rid of the Jews-- take their assets, get rid of them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they were not ready yet to kill them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That only event happened after the Evian conference, when Hitler saw that the Western powers were not in the slightest interested in the fate of Jews.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And he knew he had a free hand.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "His ambassador came back and said, you can do what you like.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That was a serious accusation for the Western nations.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I must say, as an interesting interruption here, I've seen a film, a documentary film on the BBC.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I can't remember its title.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It had to do with the Hungarian Jews' negotiations of 10,000 trucks for a million Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The story is well-documented in books and otherwise, so I'm not going to go into it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But there was a very interesting comment at the end of that film, which said that even if the deal would have gone through, which was most unlikely because the allies wouldn't have agreed and so on, who would've taken a million Jews?",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody wanted to.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is absolutely true.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
